The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Shome best in ABP sports
 BY A STAFF REPORTER  Rajib Shome with his ABP sports best athletes trophy at Mohammedan Sporting ground Sunday Calcutta: The 42nd edition of the Ananda Bazar Patrika annual sports was held at Mohammedan Sporting ground Sunday. The meet attracted an nearly 700 participants. Rajib Shome of advertisement department emerged the best sportsperson of the meet for his allround show. He won the 200m and 400m dashes, while finished second in shot put. In the much-anticipated tug-of-war, administration department defeated marketing services in the final. ABP News finished third. Manufacturing department won the relay race. Marketing services and ABP News finished second and third, respectively. In the fun-filled fancy dress competition, Tanya Guptas performance as Charlie Chaplin fetched her the title. Anirban Banik (sumo wrestler) and Pratyusha Ghatak (lady hawker) came second and third.  Copyright 
